<i>The one thing Trainor
didn't count on...</i>

256
00:15:59.158 --> 00:16:00.592
Sweet mother of God.

257
00:16:00.726 --> 00:16:02.058
<i>Was a stowaway.</i>

258
00:16:02.128 --> 00:16:03.596
Hold on. there's
something up here.

259
00:16:03.663 --> 00:16:05.040
[air control] <i>You're
breaking up. Larry.</i>

260
00:16:05.064 --> 00:16:06.396
<i>Say again. Repeat.</i>

261
00:16:06.466 --> 00:16:07.559
Hold on. [groans]

262
00:16:19.612 --> 00:16:20.841
[alarms beeping]

263
00:16:22.849 --> 00:16:24.818
<i>Larry. do you
read? Let's pull it up.</i>

264
00:16:24.917 --> 00:16:25.917
[muttering]

265
00:16:26.919 --> 00:16:28.353
<i>Put some G on it. Larry.</i>

266
00:16:28.654 --> 00:16:30.646
<i>Larry! Larry. do you read?</i>

267
00:16:31.324 --> 00:16:32.587
<i>Larry. come in.</i>

268
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:36.921
<i>He's not responding.</i>

269
00:16:37.997 --> 00:16:39.260
[men shouting]

270
00:16:58.684 --> 00:17:01.518
[Mr. Morden] <i>What man
possessed of what grit</i>

271
00:17:01.621 --> 00:17:03.783
<i>could survive such a fall?</i>

272
00:17:05.091 --> 00:17:06.992
<i>Or was our golden boy</i>

273
00:17:07.059 --> 00:17:09.961
<i>newly possessed
of something else?</i>

274
00:17:19.505 --> 00:17:22.304
<i>Larry crawled from
the wreckage that day.</i>

275
00:17:22.375 --> 00:17:23.809
<i>forever changed.</i>

276
00:17:24.544 --> 00:17:26.376
<i>in ways that would
take him decades</i>

277
00:17:26.479 --> 00:17:29.244
<i>to even begin to understand.</i>

278
00:17:30.983 --> 00:17:32.583
- [mechanical whirring]
- [boot clanking]

279
00:17:44.363 --> 00:17:47.094
It is so important
what you're doing. Cliff.

280
00:17:47.199 --> 00:17:49.691
But you know. there's
always tomorrow.

281
00:17:51.337 --> 00:17:52.896
