00:49:23.894 --> 00:49:24.987
Daddy's home.

773
00:49:28.065 --> 00:49:30.125
[Niles] I warned
you not to leave.

774
00:49:30.234 --> 00:49:31.566
I begged you.

775
00:49:32.636 --> 00:49:35.231
You have no idea
what you've done.

776
00:49:35.506 --> 00:49:37.134
It wasn't that bad.

777
00:49:37.975 --> 00:49:41.605
<i>"Bad" doesn't begin to describe
what befell Cloverton today. Bill.</i>

778
00:49:41.745 --> 00:49:43.145
[Bill] <i>Thank you. Wendy.</i>

779
00:49:44.915 --> 00:49:47.817
[Mr. Morden] <i>It's always
uncomfortable. isn't it.</i>

780
00:49:48.152 --> 00:49:49.677
<i>when Daddy gets scared?</i>

781
00:49:50.955 --> 00:49:52.753
<i>As well he should be.</i>

782
00:49:53.190 --> 00:49:56.092
<i>Niles Caulder should
be shitting his pants.</i>

783
00:49:56.927 --> 00:49:58.156
<i>He knows what's coming.</i>

784
00:49:58.295 --> 00:49:59.820
<i>He'd be a fool not to.</i>

785
00:50:00.164 --> 00:50:03.157
<i>You don't spend decades
tap dancing on hornets' nests.</i>

786
00:50:03.267 --> 00:50:05.259
<i>and not expect to be stung.</i>

787
00:50:06.437 --> 00:50:07.996
<i>Niles Caulder had enemies.</i>

788
00:50:10.274 --> 00:50:13.108
<i>Enemies he could
no longer hide from.</i>

789
00:50:13.844 --> 00:50:15.506
[Niles] Whether
you realize it or not.

790
00:50:16.180 --> 00:50:17.180
your actions...

791
00:50:17.281 --> 00:50:20.376
Your actions have consequences.

792
00:50:20.551 --> 00:50:25.012
and those consequences
are coming to this house.

793
00:50:25.389 --> 00:50:26.687
to the town.

794
00:50:27.391 --> 00:50:28.391
[Niles sighs]

795
00:50:28.459 --> 00:50:29.825
Of that. there's no doubt.

796
00:50:29.960 --> 00:50:31.826
You really think
we're in danger. Chief?

797
00:50:31.962 --> 00:50:33.294
That we need to pick up and run?

798
00:50:33.364 --> 00:50:34.957
That's what you
really. really think?

799
00:50:35.032 --> 00:50:36.694
As far away as possible.

800
00:50:37.334 --> 00:50:38.666
as soon as we can.

801
00:50:38.969 --> 00:50:40.494
What happens to the town?

802
00:50:40.571 --> 00:50:42.733
The town is not my main concern.

803
00:50:42.840 --> 00:50:44.001
So. the town gets screwed?

804
00:50:44.074 --> 00:50:47.306
You've done quite
enough to this town.

805
00:50:47.378 --> 00:50:48.402
thank you.

806
00:50:49.013 --> 00:50:50.174
This is bullshit.

807
00:50:50.314 --> 00:50:51.594
[Niles] Don't you start with me.

808
00:50:51.649 --> 00:50:52.844
You and I both know

809
00:50:52.917 --> 00:50:55.910
this field trip was for little
more than your own amusement.

810
00:50:56.520 --> 00:50:57.886
[Cliff] So. now
she's the bad guy?

811
00:50:57.988 --> 00:51:00.685
Okay. let's talk
about you. Chief.

812
00:51:01.325 --> 00:51:03.521
You told me my
daughter was dead!

813
00:51:04.929 --> 00:51:06.363
I was trying to protect you.

814
00:51:06.864 --> 00:51:08.162
[Cliff] By lying?

815
00:51:08.232 --> 00:51:10.497
I'm trying to protect you now.

816
00:51:11.735 --> 00:51:13.647
Do you honestly think she
would have accepted you?

817
00:51:13.671 --> 00:51:15.139
[Cliff] Did I get
a chance to try?

818
00:51:15.272 --> 00:51:17.207
She lost her mother. her father.

819
00:51:17.274 --> 00:51:19.004
I don't know if she
would have accepted me.

820
00:51:19.176 --> 00:51:21.042
You robbed me of that chance.

821
00:51:22.446 --> 00:51:24.108
What am I to her now?

822
00:51:25.382 --> 00:51:26.577
I'm nothing.

823
00:51:27.184 --> 00:51:28.345
I'm a monster.

824
00:51:29.186 --> 00:51:31.917
I assure you. there are
many monsters in this world.

825
00:51:32.690 --> 00:51:34.022
and none of them.

826
00:51:35.426 --> 00:51:37.258
not a one. is you.

827
00:51:43.033 --> 00:51:44.763
I've tried so hard
to shield you.

828
00:51:46.604 --> 00:51:48.368
And I know what I'm asking you.

829
00:51:49.206 --> 00:51:51.903
To leave the safest
place you've ever known.

830
00:51:52.443 --> 00:51:55.538
to step out into the world
that would rather ignore you.

831
00:51:56.213 --> 00:51:57.408
shun you.

832
00:51:57.715 --> 00:51:59.047
belittle you.

833
00:52:00.084 --> 00:52:01.746
But if you stay here.

834
00:52:02.386 --> 00:52:03.547
if we die now.

835
00:52:03.654 --> 00:52:08.092
then this magical experiment.

836
00:52:08.192 --> 00:52:10.661
this you.

837
00:52:12.329 --> 00:52:14.059
my life accomplishments.

838
00:52:14.898 --> 00:52:16.059
all.

839
00:52:16.333 --> 00:52:17.699
it will just...

840
00:52:20.838 --> 00:52:21.931
It will...

841
00:52:25.943 --> 00:52:28.139
[Cliff] Or we don't
abandon the town.

842
00:52:28.245 --> 00:52:30.942
We protect them from
these so-called enemies.

843
00:52:31.115 --> 00:52:32.276
We fight.

844
00:52:32.349 --> 00:52:33.510
We could.

845
00:52:34.585 --> 00:52:36.144
But we'd be doomed.

846
00:52:36.286 --> 00:52:37.811
[Cliff] What are we now?

847
00:52:42.026 --> 00:52:43.688
[Larry] I'm going
to go with the Chief.

848
00:52:45.629 --> 00:52:46.688
Agreed.

849
00:52:55.539 --> 00:52:56.539
Fuck it.

850
00:52:57.541 --> 00:52:58.541
Shotgun.

851
00:53:41.051 --> 00:53:42.485
Hey. for the record.

852
00:53:42.553 --> 00:53:44.112
the town can kiss my ass.

853
00:53:44.421 --> 00:53:46.515
But that doesn't mean Cliff
should go in there alone.

854
00:53:46.590 --> 00:53:48.252
It's over. Jane. Let it go.

855
00:53:48.525 --> 00:53:50.585
Okay. except I
vote we turn around.

856
00:53:50.728 --> 00:53:52.594
- No.
- Rita?

857
00:53:52.696 --> 00:53:56.224
I can't promise I won't.
you know. be disgusting.

858
00:53:57.101 --> 00:53:58.330
But. yes.

859
00:53:58.435 --> 00:53:59.435
[Larry groans]

860
00:54:00.204 --> 00:54:01.228
Larry?

861
00:54:02.272 --> 00:54:03.331
Larry's a yes.

862
00:54:03.540 --> 00:54:04.540
Whoo!

863
00:54:39.376 --> 00:54:40.605
This is wrong.

864
00:54:41.211 --> 00:54:42.406
Might be.

865
00:54:43.080 --> 00:54:44.412
Probably is.

866
00:54:46.250 --> 00:54:47.250
We'll be back.

867
00:55:29.426 --> 00:55:30.666
[Mr. Morden] <i>And there they go.</i>

868
00:55:30.794 --> 00:55:32.786
<i>our four lovable losers.</i>

869
00:55:32.930 --> 00:55:35.991
<i>banding together to become
the superhero fighting force</i>

870
00:55:36.099 --> 00:55:39.263
<i>no one saw coming
except everybody.</i>

871
00:55:39.436 --> 00:55:40.665
<i>But fear not.</i>

872
00:55:41.138 --> 00:55:43.266
<i>There's a way out of this dreck.</i>

873
00:55:43.340 --> 00:55:44.467
<i>Follow me.</i>

874
00:55:44.608 --> 00:55:45.837
[rumbling]

875
00:55:45.943 --> 00:55:47.104
It's fine.

876
00:55:48.779 --> 00:55:50.111
It's totally fine.

877
00:55:52.683 --> 00:55:54.151
Paraguay.

878
00:55:54.218 --> 00:55:55.686
Yes. Niles.

879
00:55:55.786 --> 00:55:57.118
Paraguay.

880
00:55:57.788 --> 00:56:00.451
Always. Paraguay.

881
00:56:01.692 --> 00:56:02.955
Morden.

882
00:56:03.060 --> 00:56:04.153
Sure.

883
00:56:04.294 --> 00:56:05.294
But not.

884
00:56:05.362 --> 00:56:06.922
I mean. I haven't
been Mr. Morden since.

885
00:56:06.964 --> 00:56:07.964
"Ahh!

886
00:56:08.465 --> 00:56:09.728
No! Help me."

887
00:56:10.534 --> 00:56:11.627
[laughs]

888
00:56:11.702 --> 00:56:13.462
- [rock music playing]
- [rumbling continues]

889
00:56:23.013 --> 00:56:24.013
[farting loudly]

890
00:56:42.432 --> 00:56:45.027
I've been admiring
your friends. Niles.

891
00:56:45.102 --> 00:56:47.537
those freaks of yours.
for quite some time.

892
00:56:47.604 --> 00:56:49.539
Don't you dare hurt them.

893
00:56:49.606 --> 00:56:50.733
Hurt them? No.

894
00:56:51.241 --> 00:56:52.539
That wouldn't be any fun.

895
00:56:52.676 --> 00:56:53.871
[laughs] No.

896
00:56:53.944 --> 00:56:55.822
That would be quite the
same old story. wouldn't it?

897
00:56:55.846 --> 00:56:58.509
I think we're gonna do
something different this time.

898
00:57:01.018 --> 00:57:03.010
You were right in
one respect. however.

899
00:57:04.955 --> 00:57:06.355
They are quite doomed.

900
00:57:06.623 --> 00:57:07.750
[Cliff] What the fuck?
